cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.MM 

This paper deals with face classification using both traditional computer vision techniques and deep neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of machine learning models for classification also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The comparison of human and machine performance on the task of fine-grained race classification involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of deep neural networks for classification suggests the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of a face database and the focus on facial features suggests the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
